.TH @PACKAGE@ 1 "January 2025" "version @VERSION@" "User Manuals"
.SH "NAME"
@PACKAGE@ \- Super Simple Multicast DNS server
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.B @PACKAGE@ [-n host_alias_override] [-4] [-i <only interface>] [-p <pid file>] [-v] [-f]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.B @PACKAGE@ is a Super Simple Multicast DNS server, able to reply to other computers on the network at (your hostname).local
.SH "OPTIONS"
Usually this is intended to be used without any -n flag.
.IP -n
Specify a hostname override instead of using /etc/hostname - you can launch multiple instances, to get multiple overrides.
.IP -i
Specify a an interface name for which to listen on rather than all interfaces (default).
.IP -f
Run the @PACKAGE@ in the foreground
.IP -p
Specify a file system path to store the program's PID. If set, subsequent executions using the same path will verify that an instance of the program is not already running.IP
.IP -4
Disable IPv6 operation.
.IP -v
Increase program verbosity.
